This paper deals with topic modeling and evaluation of cultural-scale claims, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, the paper discusses the sensitivity of topic models to sampling effects, which is relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), deep learning (cs.DL), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
